modules.description: This module implements a rasterizer for vector graphics, converting SVG paths into pixel-based images. It provides functions to create and manipulate rasterization contexts, supporting operations like rendering shapes with specified colors and transformations. Use it to generate bitmaps from vector paths or integrate SVG rendering into graphical applications.

Handles image data transformations and metadata extraction for SVG rendering. Works with image data structures containing width, height, and transformation matrices. Used to retrieve dimensional properties and apply geometric transformations to images within SVG contexts.

This module provides operations for parsing vector graphics data into structured geometric representations and converting them into pixel-based images. It works with data structures like paths, gradients, and layout attributes, handling transformations and unit conversions during rendering. Key use cases include generating scalable images from SVG descriptions and processing vector graphics for display with resolution-independent quality.
